n.</pos> <conjf>Eking</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[AS. <ets>⟦emac⟧kan</ets>,
<ets>⟦ymac⟧kan</ets>; akin to OFries. <ets>⟦amac⟧ka</ets>, OS.
<ets>⟦omac⟧kian</ets>, OHG. <ets>ouhh⟦omac⟧n</ets> to add, Icel.
<ets>auka</ets> to increase, Sw. <ets>⟦oum⟧ka</ets>, Dan.
<ets>⟦oum⟧ge</ets>, Goth. <ets>aukan</ets>, L. <ets>augere</ets>, Skr.
<ets>⟦omac⟧jas</ets> strength, <ets>ugra</ets> mighty, and probably to
English <ets>wax</ets>, v. i. Cf. <er>Augment</er>,
<er>Nickname</er>.]</ety> <def>To increase; to add to; to augment; --
now commonly used with <ptcl>out</ptcl>, the notion conveyed being to
add to, or piece out by a laborious, inferior, or scanty addition;
<as>as, to <ex>eke</ex> out a scanty supply of one kind with some
other</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧To <xex>eke</xex> my pain.⟦rdquo⟧
